    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Some people are pushing the non forked version of the testnet faster than the fork is going. This causes Geth to fast sync to the other chain, then fail since it's bad. We didn't implement fast sync fork protection into these hard forks because there was no incentive to keep the other chain alive. We didn't really think about the testnet being pushed by people who just don't care. Please use develop (it has added logic) to work around this.\n",
